  "text": "Comparison is also made with the North America Regional Reanalysis (NARR) soil moisture products using the Noah Land Community Model [CITATION_1] . NARR assimilates observed precipitation, which, from the hydrology stand, is a significant improvement over other reanalysis products. Plotted in Fig. 4 (the third row) is the 25-yr (1979-2004) monthly mean soil moisture. NARR predicts much wetter conditions in the western half of the domain, as seen in the transects. Over the eastern half of the domain, NARR is wetter in the top 10 cm, but is very similar to SMC in the top 2 m.",
